 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "theoretical-foundation",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🧭 Cross-Absolute Selection Principle (CASP)\n",
    "\n",
    "## 📘 Formal Definition\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Definition (CASP):** A mediated interaction between two Absolute Entities is valid if and only if it:\n",
    "> 1. Minimizes the cross-absolute interaction action\n",
    "> 2. Maintains entropic compatibility within tolerance δ\n",
    "> 3. Maximizes directional coherence\n",
    "> 4. Satisfies irreducibility constraints\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🔬 Theoretical Context\n",
    "This notebook builds directly on the transfinite mediators from `05_transfinite_interaction_chains.ipynb`, extending our understanding of ontological interaction mechanisms.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🌐 Ontological Derivation\n",
    "The Cross-Absolute Selection Principle emerges from the fundamental axioms of:\n",
    "- Irreducibility of Absolute Entities\n",
    "- Entropy Scalar Conservation\n",
    "- Mediation Legality in Transfinite Spaces\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🔮 Transfinite Interaction Chains (TIC) Constraint\n",
    "All CASP evaluations are subordinate to the entropy trajectory constraint:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\epsilon_{n+1} \\geq \\epsilon_n $$\n",
    "\n",
    "Ensuring monotonic information preservation across interaction hierarchies."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "essential-imports",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Advanced Scientific Computing Imports\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import scipy.optimize as optimize\n",
    "import sympy as sp\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configuration\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\n",
    "np.set_printoptions(precision=6, suppress=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "symbolic-representation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Symbolic Representation of CASP\n",
    "def symbolic_casp_representation(n):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Generate symbolic representation of CASP for theoretical exploration.\"\"\"\n",
    "    # Define symbolic matrix variables\n",
    "    S1 = sp.MatrixSymbol('S1', n, n)\n",
    "    S2 = sp.MatrixSymbol('S2', n, n)\n",
    "    M = sp.MatrixSymbol('M', n, n)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Symbolic action definition\n",
    "    action = sp.trace(S1 * M * S2.T * S2 * M.T * S1.T)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'S1': S1,\n",
    "        'S2': S2,\n",
    "        'M': M,\n",
    "        'action': action\n",
    "    }"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "absolute-entity",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class CASPViolation(Exception):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Custom exception for CASP interaction violations.\"\"\"\n",
    "    pass\n",
    "\n",
    "class AbsoluteEntity:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Representation of an Absolute Entity with rigorous ontological constraints.\"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self, signature, state, tolerance=1e-6):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        Initialize an Absolute Entity with comprehensive validation.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Args:\n",
    "            signature (np.ndarray): Symmetric signature matrix\n",
    "            state (np.ndarray): Entity state vector\n",
    "            tolerance (float): Ontological compatibility tolerance\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        # Rigorous signature validation\n",
    "        if not isinstance(signature, np.ndarray):\n",
    "            raise TypeError(\"Signature must be a NumPy array\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if signature.shape[0] != signature.shape[1]:\n",
    "            raise ValueError(\"Signature must be a square matrix\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if not np.allclose(signature, signature.T, atol=tolerance):\n",
    "            raise ValueError(\"Signature matrix must be symmetric\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if state.shape[0] != signature.shape[0]:\n",
    "            raise ValueError(\"State vector dimension must match signature\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        self.signature = signature\n",
    "        self.state = state\n",
    "        self.tolerance = tolerance\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Compute entropy with ontological constraints\n",
    "        self.entropy = np.trace(signature @ signature.T)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Ensure state vector normalization\n",
    "        self.normalized_state = state / np.linalg.norm(state)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __repr__(self):\n",
    "        return f\"AbsoluteEntity(Entropy: {self.entropy:.6f}, State Norm: {np.linalg.norm(self.state):.6f})\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "mediator-construction",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def construct_mediation_space(a_dim, b_dim, complexity=0.5, seed=None):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Generate a mediation space projection with ontological complexity parameter.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        a_dim (int): Source space dimension\n",
    "        b_dim (int): Target space dimension\n",
    "        complexity (float): Mediation potential [0.1, 1.0]\n",
    "        seed (int, optional): Reproducibility seed\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        np.ndarray: Orthonormal mediator matrix\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    if not 0.1 <= complexity <= 1.0:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(\"Complexity must be in [0.1, 1.0]\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Complexity-weighted random matrix generation\n",
    "    M = rng.normal(0, complexity, (a_dim, b_dim))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # QR decomposition for orthonormalization\n",
    "    Q, _ = np.linalg.qr(M)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return Q[:, :b_dim]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "casp-evaluation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def optimize_mediator(entity_a, entity_b, initial_complexity=0.5, max_iterations=100):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Optimize mediator to minimize cross-absolute interaction action.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        entity_a (AbsoluteEntity): First absolute entity\n",
    "        entity_b (AbsoluteEntity): Second absolute entity\n",
    "        initial_complexity (float): Starting mediation complexity\n",
    "        max_iterations (int): Maximum optimization iterations\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        dict: Optimization results with optimal mediator and metrics\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    def objective_function(complexity):\n",
    "        mediator = construct_mediation_space(\n",
    "            entity_a.signature.shape[0], \n",
    "            entity_b.signature.shape[0], \n",
    "            complexity\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        result = evaluate_casp(entity_a, entity_b, mediator)\n",
    "        return result['InteractionAction']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Scipy differential evolution for global optimization\n",
    "    result = optimize.differential_evolution(\n",
    "        objective_function, \n",
    "        bounds=[(0.1, 1.0)],\n",
    "        maxiter=max_iterations\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    optimal_complexity = result.x[0]\n",
    "    optimal_mediator = construct_mediation_space(\n",
    "        entity_a.signature.shape[0], \n",
    "        entity_b.signature.shape[0], \n",
    "        optimal_complexity\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'OptimalMediator': optimal_mediator,\n",
    "        'OptimalComplexity': optimal_complexity,\n",
    "        'MinimumAction': result.fun\n",
    "    }"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "interaction-evaluation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def evaluate_casp(entity_a, entity_b, mediator, tolerance=1e-6):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Comprehensive CASP interaction evaluation.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        entity_a (AbsoluteEntity): First absolute entity\n",
    "        entity_b (AbsoluteEntity): Second absolute entity\n",
    "        mediator (np.ndarray): Interaction mediator matrix\n",
    "        tolerance (float): Ontological compatibility threshold\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        dict: Detailed interaction metrics\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Information tensor computation\n",
    "    I = entity_a.signature @ mediator @ entity_b.signature.T\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Frobenius norm as interaction action\n",
    "    interaction_action = np.linalg.norm(I, ord='fro')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Entropy gap with leak computation\n",
    "    trace_proj = np.trace(I @ I.T)\n",
    "    entropy_gap = abs(entity_a.entropy - trace_proj)\n",
    "    entropy_leak = entropy_gap / entity_a.entropy\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Normalized coherence index (cosine similarity)\n",
    "    projected_a = (entity_a.signature @ mediator).flatten()\n",
    "    projected_b = entity_b.signature.flatten()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    coherence_index = cosine_similarity(\n",
    "        projected_a.reshape(1, -1), \n",
    "        projected_b.reshape(1, -1)\n",
    "    )[0, 0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # State vector directional alignment\n",
    "    state_alignment = np.dot(entity_a.normalized_state, entity_b.normalized_state)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Interaction classification\n",
    "    if entropy_leak > tolerance or coherence_index < 0:\n",
    "        interaction_type = \"Entropic Conflict\"\n",
    "    elif coherence_index > 0.9:\n",
    "        interaction_type = \"Resonant Convergence\"\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        interaction_type = \"Directional Modulation\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    results = {\n",
    "        'InformationTensor': I,\n",
    "        'InteractionAction': interaction_action,\n",
    "        'EntropyGap': entropy_gap,\n",
    "        'EntropyLeak': entropy_leak,\n",
    "        'CoherenceIndex': coherence_index,\n",
    "        'StateAlignment': state_alignment,\n",
    "        'InteractionType': interaction_type\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Optional CASP validation\n",
    "    if entropy_leak > tolerance or coherence_index < 0:\n",
    "        raise CASPViolation(f\"Interaction Invalid: {interaction_type}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "comprehensive-simulation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Comprehensive CASP Simulation\n",
    "def run_casp_simulation(n_entities=2, dim=4):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Execute a comprehensive CASP simulation.\"\"\"\n",
    "    entities = [\n",
    "        AbsoluteEntity(\n",
    "            signature=np.random.rand(dim, dim),\n",
    "            state=np.random.rand(dim)\n",
    "        ) for _ in range(n_entities)\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    results_table = []\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(n_entities):\n",
    "        for j in range(i+1, n_entities):\n",
    "            # Optimized mediator search\n",
    "            optimization_result = optimize_mediator(entities[i], entities[j])\n",
    "            \n",
    "            try:\n",
    "                casp_evaluation = evaluate_casp(\n",
    "                    entities[i], entities[j], \n",
    "                    optimization_result['OptimalMediator']\n",
    "                )\n",
    "                \n",
    "                results_table.append({\n",
    "                    'Entity 1': repr(entities[i]),\n",
    "                    'Entity 2': repr(entities[j]),\n",
    "                    'Optimal Complexity': optimization_result['OptimalComplexity'],\n",
    "                    'Interaction Action': casp_evaluation['InteractionAction'],\n",
    "                    'Entropy Gap': casp_evaluation['EntropyGap'],\n",
    "                    'Coherence Index': casp_evaluation['CoherenceIndex'],\n",
    "                    'Interaction Type': casp_evaluation['InteractionType']\n",
    "                })\n",
    "            except CASPViolation as e:\n",
    "                print(f\"CASP Violation: {e}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return results_table"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "final-execution",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Execute Comprehensive Simulation\n",
    "simulation_results = run_casp_simulation()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display Results Tabularly\n",
    "print(\"\\n🔬 CASP Interaction Analysis Results\")\n",
    "for result in simulation_results:\n",
    "    print(\"\\n\" + \"-\"*50)\n",
    "    for key, value in result.items():\n",
    "        print(f\"{key}: {value}\")"
   ]
  },
